==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Flotage
<hw>Flo"tage</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OF.
<ets>flotage</ets>, F. <ets>flottage</ets>, fr. <ets>flotter</ets> to
float.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The state of floating.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which floats on the sea or in rivers.</def>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>floatage</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Flotant</ent>⟦br⟧
